{"bookResponse":{"bookId":"2ad4ecbb8e24f6cd9efcac897a233cf2","locale":"en_US","title":"macOS User Guide","meta":{"productVersion":"13.0","platformOSVersion":"13.0","icon":"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/058e4af8e726290f491044219d2eee73.png","build_date":"Wed Mar 22 20:19:57 GMT 2023","product":"mac-help","creationDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","framework":"duck-15.4.0:goose-2.15.4:cuckoo-4.2.0"},"tocId":"MH43558","bookInfo":{"versionsDetails":[{"productVersion":"14.0","displayVersion":"macOS Sonoma 14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"14.0"},{"productVersion":"13.0","displayVersion":"macOS Ventura 13","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"13.0"},{"productVersion":"12.0","displayVersion":"macOS Monterey 12","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"12.0"},{"productVersion":"11.0","displayVersion":"macOS Big Sur 11.0","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"11.0"},{"productVersion":"10.15","displayVersion":"macOS Catalina 10.15","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.15"},{"productVersion":"10.14","displayVersion":"macOS Mojave 10.14","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.14"},{"productVersion":"10.13","displayVersion":"macOS High Sierra","platform":"mac","platformOSVersion":"10.13"}]},"articles":[{"articleId":{"id":"BK_2AD4ECBB8E24F6CD9EFCAC897A233CF2_MCHLP2555","locale":"en_US"},"meta":{"createDate":"Fri Mar 24 07:00:00 GMT 2023","lastModifiedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","publishedDate":"Mon Mar 27 17:01:20 GMT 2023","contentType":"book","archive":"false","ownerName":"apd migration","modifiedBy":"apd migration","version":"1","unPublished":false,"contentModel":"book"},"content":{"main":{"title":"Learn how passwords are used on Mac","summary":"Keep your Mac secure using a login password, Apple ID password, and web passwords and passkeys, and use a keychain to store your passwords securely."},"sections":[{"level":"1","text":"<body dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mchlp2555\" class=\"AppleTopic apd-topic dark-mode-enabled\" data-istaskopen=\"true\" data-designversion=\"2\" lang=\"en\"><a name=\"mchlp2555\"></a><figure class=\"topicIcon\"><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/a7cf9b42a4eb346015f47a47546a61a2.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Keychain.png\"></figure><h1>Learn how passwords are used on Mac</h1><p>macOS is designed to keep your information safe and secure. The security of your Mac depends a great deal on using secure passwords in key areas.</p><div id=\"mchlp9f26e83\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Login password</h2><p>A login password, also called a<em> user password</em>, allows you to log in and access the information on your Mac. When you create your login password, be sure it’s easily memorable, write it down, and keep it in a secure location.</p></div><div id=\"mchlpbdc3246\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Apple ID password</h2><p>An <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=apple-id&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOSBDC8E694&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">Apple ID</a> gives you access to the iTunes Store, the App Store, Apple Books, iCloud, FaceTime, and other Apple services. It consists of an email address (for example, daniel_rico1@icloud.com) and a password. Apple recommends you use the same Apple ID for all Apple services. When you create your Apple ID password, be sure it’s easily memorable, write it down, and keep it in a secure location. If you can’t remember your Apple ID password, see <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=if-you-forget-your-apple-id-or-password&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLCA50AA6A&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">If you forget your Apple ID or password</a>.</p><p>You can also use your Apple ID to reset your login password if you forget it. Sign in to your <a href=\"https://appleid.apple.com\" class=\"URL\">Apple ID account page</a>.</p></div><div id=\"mchlba043c50\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Website passwords</h2><p>When you need to create a password for a website, Safari suggests a unique, hard-to-guess (or “strong”) password. It’s recommended that you use the suggested password or <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=create-a-passkey&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHL4AF65D1A&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">create a passkey</a>. Passwords and <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=passkey&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=GLOS0930F77C&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0&amp;aside=true\" class=\"xRef Aside\">passkeys</a> are saved in a keychain, then automatically filled the next time you need to sign in.</p><p>To view or change passwords and passkeys you’ve saved for websites, use Passwords settings. Choose Apple menu <picture><source media=\"(not all)\" srcset=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/0e2c53fa5a413cc7ff5099226fb50188.png\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11~dark.png\"></source><img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/2f77cc85238452e25cb517130188bf99.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"24\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/IL_AppleLogo_11.png\"></picture> &gt; System Settings, then click Passwords <img src=\"https://help.apple.com/assets/63BCA927AAE78C58DD7FBE35/63BCA92EAAE78C58DD7FBE76/en_US/40ff588be3beaa4acaf19d4beeba4177.png\" alt=\"\" height=\"30\" width=\"30\" originalImageName=\"SharedGlobalArt/AppIconTopic_Passwords.png\"> in the sidebar. (You may need to scroll down.)</p></div><div id=\"mchl5e4eeb3e\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">Password keychains</h2><p>A keychain saves your passwords and fills them in automatically when you sign in to websites, apps, and services. You can store passwords in Keychain Access and iCloud Keychain.</p><ul><li><p><em>Keychain Access: </em>Keychain Access stores passwords for various apps and services for your Mac. Your keychain password (which unlocks your keychain) is set to match the login password for your Mac. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=about-your-keychain-password&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MCHLP1086&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">About your keychain password</a>.</p></li><li><p><em>iCloud Keychain: </em>iCloud Keychain keeps your passwords up to date across your Mac, iPhone, iPad, and iPod touch. It stores website and Wi-Fi passwords, and it keeps account passwords and settings that you add to Internet Accounts settings up to date on your Mac. See <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/guide/?platform=mac&amp;product=mac-help&amp;vanityname=set-icloud-keychain-autofill-information-mac&amp;version=13.0&amp;locale=en_US&amp;topicid=MH43699&amp;type=ddm&amp;platformOSVersion=13.0\" class=\"xRef AppleTopic\">Set up iCloud Keychain to autofill information</a>.</p></li></ul></div><div id=\"mchlp556862a\" class=\"Subhead\"><h2 class=\"Name\">About your recovery key</h2><p>If you encrypt the information on your Mac using FileVault, you can choose how to unlock your disk and reset your login password if you forget it: using your iCloud account or a recovery key. A recovery key is a string of letters and numbers that’s created for you. The recovery key should not be stored in the same location as the Mac, where it can be discovered.</p></div><div class=\"LinkUniversal\"><strong>See also</strong><a href=\"https://support.apple.com/HT204106\" class=\"URL\">Apple Support article: If your Apple ID is locked or disabled</a></div></body>","tags":[{"type":"audience","refKey":"PUBLIC_USERS","tagPath":"audience/PUBLIC_USERS","title":"Public"}]}]},"categoryInfo":{"categories":["IP-Meta/DesignVersion/DesignVersion2","platform/mac","DisplayVersion/macOS Ventura 13","MetaFollow/MetaFollowOFF","ContentMode/liveContent","SupportSearchIndex/SupportSearchIndexON","ArchivalStatus/Archived","ExternalIndex/ExternalIndexOFF"],"categoryDictionaries":[{"key":"SupportSearchIndexON","name":"SupportSearchIndexON","englishName":"SupportSearchIndexON","displayName":"SupportSearchIndexON","articleCount":"120736"},{"key":"liveContent","name":"Live Content","englishName":"Live Content","displayName":"Live Content","articleCount":"135880"},{"key":"IP-Meta","name":"IP-Meta","englishName":"IP-Meta","displayName":"IP-Meta","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ContentMode","name":"ContentMode","englishName":"ContentMode","displayName":"ContentMode","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion2","name":"DesignVersion 2","englishName":"DesignVersion 2","displayName":"DesignVersion 2","articleCount":"135315"},{"key":"MetaFollow","name":"MetaFollow","englishName":"MetaFollow","displayName":"MetaFollow","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndex","name":"ExternalIndex","englishName":"ExternalIndex","displayName":"ExternalIndex","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"DesignVersion","name":"DesignVersion","englishName":"DesignVersion","displayName":"DesignVersion","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"mac","name":"mac","englishName":"mac","displayName":"mac","articleCount":"85819"},{"key":"platform","name":"platform","englishName":"platform","displayName":"platform","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"Archived","name":"Archived","englishName":"Archived","displayName":"Archived","articleCount":"124678"},{"key":"ArchivalStatus","name":"ArchivalStatus","englishName":"ArchivalStatus","displayName":"ArchivalStatus","articleCount":"0"},{"key":"ExternalIndexOFF","name":"ExternalIndexOFF","englishName"